    "x 1 i (s)) = (H z 0 µ x(s) (dz), H z 1 µ x(s) (dz)), Ax:= (-x 0, d dξ x 1), D(A):= {x = (x 0, x 1) ∈ H: x 1 ∈ W 1,2 ([-d, 0]), x 1 (0) = x 0 } is a maximally dissipative operator (so Assumption 4.1 holds), b ∈ L(H), bx:= ((b 0 + 1)x 0, 0), c ∈ L(H), cx:= (c 0 x 0, 0), η ∈ L(H), ηx:= (⟨η 1, x 1 ⟩ L 2, 0), χ ∈ L(H), χx:= (⟨χ 1, x 1 ⟩ L 2, 0), e ∈ L(Λ; H), eq:= (e 0 q, 0), σ ∈ L 2 (R; H), σw:= (σ 0 w, 0)."
